<subSubSection id="1656D5448531ECF085B254257F7F01F2" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" type="description">
<paragraph id="4EBEAA9EA6ED48E626FA91D9ED203F47" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
<pageBreakToken id="95EA7625356F32A5E1E0A6C930074092" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" start="start">Description</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D9F93D7BA26E7EA985738D163D157907" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
Glabrous or puberulent herb from a deep rootstock. Stems 30(-50) cm long, numerous, trailing. Leaf blade 0.6-2 
<normalizedToken id="BFF6CDDD76A87A09F97724BA7290EBD2" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.4-1.6 cm, ovate-deltoid; base truncate and briefly cuneate onto the petiole, auricles not well-developed; apex obtuse and mucronate or acute; margin entire; petiole 4-8 (-12) mm. Flowers solitary (rarely paired), axillary, pedunculate; peduncles 10-18 mm; bracteoles 2-6 mm, linear; pedicels 2-4 mm; outer sepals 7-10 
<normalizedToken id="D723B9EF4B9A056BC9F24D83F27EABE7" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-7 mm, elliptic, obtuse; corolla (1-) 1.5 (-2) cm long, pink, shallowly lobed, midpetaline bands pilose, terminating in small teeth; ovary glabrous; style divided 4-5 mm above base, stigmas 2-3 mm. Capsule glabrous; seeds smooth but with slightly muricate angles. [
<bibRefCitation id="330BAE7093B913CD0A107D9DF66EEBBF" author="O'Donell, CA" journalOrPublisher="Boletin de la Sociedad Argentina de Botanica" pageId="208" pageNumber="209" pagination="143 - 184" refId="B247" refString="O'Donell, CA, 1957. Convolvuloideas chilenas. Boletin de la Sociedad Argentina de Botanica 6: 143 - 184" title="Convolvuloideas chilenas." volume="6" year="1957">
<normalizedToken id="AACBAFFDF3538FFBE385A6A15F1658BC" originalValue="O’Donell">O'Donell</normalizedToken>
1957
</bibRefCitation>
: 165-167 (Figure 7); 
<bibRefCitation id="5EDB98C941C6D414ECF6F75767C01983" author="O'Donell, CA" journalOrPublisher="Lilloa" pageId="208" pageNumber="209" pagination="87 - 348" refId="B248" refString="O'Donell, CA, 1959. Convolvulaceas argentinas II. Lilloa 29: 87 - 348" title="Convolvulaceas argentinas II." volume="29" year="1959">
<normalizedToken id="4CB9863F98A258120BC6DD1578841FC8" originalValue="O’Donell">O'Donell</normalizedToken>
1959
</bibRefCitation>
: 276]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="478EB39E7730ED8E5C4B0E296E98464A" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A22366C1C000A7DF550C783F47AF9A9D" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D3F180FADA7FC48B4CCCC6BF44C3271" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
Central Chile (
<emphasis id="BD47EBA1F3016750E9508726ED242018" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Morisson</emphasis>
16746, 
<emphasis id="AEEAFD3381D56C685853B71B2253C754" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Cuming</emphasis>
214, 
<emphasis id="8DA8D84BC1A13516D20CA577DA4DB9BB" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Gardner et al.</emphasis>
52, 
<emphasis id="F7EC5BE16DA48E97614369549BFB6AF7" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">UCEXC</emphasis>
43) and adjacent parts of Argentina (fide 
<bibRefCitation id="8EC4459AA67849FE940F18F4F251A881" author="O'Donell, CA" journalOrPublisher="Lilloa" pageId="208" pageNumber="209" pagination="87 - 348" refId="B248" refString="O'Donell, CA, 1959. Convolvulaceas argentinas II. Lilloa 29: 87 - 348" title="Convolvulaceas argentinas II." volume="29" year="1959">
<normalizedToken id="5D624A45766E7623947869BC6AB94056" originalValue="O’Donell">O'Donell</normalizedToken>
1959
</bibRefCitation>
: 277). 1500-2700 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4B4E57E549B1AC37E87F36B88206BDE8" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" type="notes">
<paragraph id="E86C6D6BB0482C7F60D40AF29C5693DB" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CB56D3C58ADF3936630DD70A33EFE563" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
This is an Andean species variable in indumentum with a superficial resemblance to 
<taxonomicName id="DAAEB9B95F206035ED7D66393EA10121" authorityName="L., Sp. Pl. 1: 153. 1753. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus arvensis" order="Solanales" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arvensis">
<emphasis id="BA05F657B1071C15EFE33191DB5ADC12" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Convolvulus arvensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but with much larger sepals and ovate-deltoid leaves with poorly developed basal auricles. It is also very similar to some forms of the African 
<taxonomicName id="7515254AA449A16A36AF6D28931A1432" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus sagittatus" order="Solanales" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sagittatus">
<emphasis id="0EDE96F2D807D47DB276D9D8B90801F8" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Convolvulus sagittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
